Naming this piece “Dimethyl Vessel”, after a good friend of mine. What youre seeing is a piece of bristol board that has been soaked in a Mimosa Hostilis root bark solution. Was soaked for 3 hours.  Dried. Drawn on with micron pens, a highlighter, and a white gel pen. Then the edges were burnt with a hot knife. The piece has been framed in a double glass floating frame to better display it.👁). •
•
•
•
With the frame this piece measures 9x11 inches. This unique piece is looking for a loving and understanding home. Psychonaut family preferred. Asking $222 . Half now half later is an option. I think this style of uv art (stained with MHRB) is sum of my most unique work, and it captures the true essence of G432 Artwerk. If youd like to bless your home with this piece contact me via DM. •
